# Vehicle Rental Management Platform â€” MVP Database Plan

## Overview

7 tables total. Single `users` table with a `role` column handles all three roles. Fleet managers get access to rental/customer data via `fleet_vehicle_assignments` + read access to `rental_records`.

---

## Tables & Columns

---

### 1. `users`
> Covers Admin, Customer, Fleet Manager via `role` column

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `user_id` | INTEGER | PK, AUTO | |
| `name` | TEXT | NOT NULL | |
| `email` | TEXT | UNIQUE, NOT NULL | |
| `password_hash` | TEXT | NOT NULL | bcrypt hashed |
| `phone` | TEXT | | |
| `role` | TEXT | CHECK IN ('admin','customer','fleet_manager') | controls dashboard routing |
| `driving_license_number` | TEXT | UNIQUE, nullable | customers only |
| `is_active` | BOOLEAN | DEFAULT 1 | admin can deactivate |
| `created_at` | DATETIME | DEFAULT NOW | |

**CRUD by Role:**
- **Admin:** Create any user, Read all users, Update role/status, Delete user
- **Customer:** Read own profile, Update own profile
- **Fleet Manager:** Read own profile, Update own profile

---

### 2. `vehicles`
> Managed fully by Admin

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `vehicle_id` | INTEGER | PK, AUTO | |
| `type` | TEXT | CHECK IN ('car','bike','van') | |
| `brand` | TEXT | NOT NULL | |
| `model` | TEXT | NOT NULL | |
| `fuel_type` | TEXT | CHECK IN ('petrol','diesel','electric','cng') | |
| `seating_capacity` | INTEGER | | |
| `price_per_hour` | REAL | NOT NULL | |
| `price_per_day` | REAL | NOT NULL | |
| `availability_status` | TEXT | CHECK IN ('available','rented','maintenance') | |
| `registration_number` | TEXT | UNIQUE, NOT NULL | |
| `fitness_expiry` | DATE | | |
| `insurance_expiry` | DATE | | |
| `photo_path` | TEXT | | static file path |
| `created_at` | DATETIME | DEFAULT NOW | |

**CRUD by Role:**
- **Admin:** Full CRUD
- **Fleet Manager:** Update `availability_status` only
- **Customer:** Read only (browse + filter)

---

### 3. `rental_records`
> Core booking table â€” links customers â†” vehicles â†” pricing

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `rental_id` | INTEGER | PK, AUTO | |
| `customer_id` | INTEGER | FK â†’ users(user_id) | role must be 'customer' |
| `vehicle_id` | INTEGER | FK â†’ vehicles(vehicle_id) | |
| `pricing_rule_id` | INTEGER | FK â†’ pricing_rules(rule_id), nullable | applied rule if any |
| `start_datetime` | DATETIME | NOT NULL | |
| `end_datetime` | DATETIME | NOT NULL | expected return |
| `actual_return_datetime` | DATETIME | nullable | set on actual return |
| `total_cost` | REAL | | calculated at booking |
| `payment_mode` | TEXT | CHECK IN ('cash','card','upi') | |
| `payment_status` | TEXT | CHECK IN ('pending','paid','refunded') | |
| `rental_status` | TEXT | CHECK IN ('booked','picked_up','returned','cancelled') | |
| `created_at` | DATETIME | DEFAULT NOW | |

**CRUD by Role:**
- **Customer:** Create (book), Read own records, Update (cancel before pickup)
- **Admin:** Read all, Update status/payment, Delete
- **Fleet Manager:** Read (vehicles they manage â€” via fleet_vehicle_assignments)

---

### 4. `pricing_rules`
> Set by Admin, applied during booking cost calculation

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `rule_id` | INTEGER | PK, AUTO | |
| `rule_name` | TEXT | NOT NULL | e.g., "Weekend Surge" |
| `rule_type` | TEXT | CHECK IN ('seasonal','weekend','late_fee','coupon') | |
| `multiplier` | REAL | DEFAULT 1.0 | e.g., 1.5 = 50% extra |
| `flat_fee` | REAL | DEFAULT 0 | e.g., late return flat charge |
| `discount_code` | TEXT | UNIQUE, nullable | for coupon type |
| `discount_percent` | REAL | nullable | e.g., 10 = 10% off |
| `valid_from` | DATE | | |
| `valid_to` | DATE | | |
| `is_active` | BOOLEAN | DEFAULT 1 | |

**CRUD by Role:**
- **Admin:** Full CRUD
- **Customer:** Read active rules (to see discounts)

---

### 5. `maintenance_logs`
> Logged by Fleet Manager for vehicles they manage

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `log_id` | INTEGER | PK, AUTO | |
| `vehicle_id` | INTEGER | FK â†’ vehicles(vehicle_id) | |
| `fleet_manager_id` | INTEGER | FK â†’ users(user_id) | role must be 'fleet_manager' |
| `maintenance_type` | TEXT | CHECK IN ('routine','repair','inspection','cleaning') | |
| `description` | TEXT | | |
| `cost` | REAL | | |
| `maintenance_date` | DATE | NOT NULL | |
| `next_due_date` | DATE | | |

**CRUD by Role:**
- **Fleet Manager:** Full CRUD on logs for their assigned vehicles
- **Admin:** Read all, Delete

---

### 6. `fleet_vehicle_assignments`
> Links which fleet manager manages which vehicle. Also allows fleet managers to view related customer rental data.

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `assignment_id` | INTEGER | PK, AUTO | |
| `fleet_manager_id` | INTEGER | FK â†’ users(user_id) | |
| `vehicle_id` | INTEGER | FK â†’ vehicles(vehicle_id) | |
| `assigned_date` | DATE | DEFAULT NOW | |
| `is_active` | BOOLEAN | DEFAULT 1 | |

**Purpose:**
- Admin assigns vehicles to fleet managers
- Fleet manager can only view/update **their assigned vehicles**
- Fleet manager can see `rental_records` WHERE `vehicle_id` IN their assignments â†’ **this is how they see customer booking info from their dashboard**

**CRUD by Role:**
- **Admin:** Full CRUD (assign/unassign)
- **Fleet Manager:** Read only

---

### 7. `notifications` *(lightweight, recommended)*
> Keeps all roles informed of important events

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `notification_id` | INTEGER | PK, AUTO | |
| `user_id` | INTEGER | FK â†’ users(user_id) | recipient |
| `message` | TEXT | NOT NULL | |
| `is_read` | BOOLEAN | DEFAULT 0 | |
| `created_at` | DATETIME | DEFAULT NOW | |

**Examples:**
- Customer: "Your booking is confirmed"
- Fleet Manager: "Vehicle V-102 is due for maintenance"
- Admin: "New booking created by customer John"

---

## Relationships (ER Summary)

```mermaid
erDiagram
    users ||--o{ rental_records : "books (customer)"
    users ||--o{ maintenance_logs : "logs (fleet_manager)"
    users ||--o{ fleet_vehicle_assignments : "assigned to"
    users ||--o{ notifications : "receives"
    vehicles ||--o{ rental_records : "is rented in"
    vehicles ||--o{ maintenance_logs : "has"
    vehicles ||--o{ fleet_vehicle_assignments : "managed by"
    pricing_rules ||--o{ rental_records : "applied to"
```

